cs.CR, cs.AR, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.SY

The paper deals with investigating and measuring speculative execution vulnerabilities, which are a type of security vulnerability. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves microprocessor implementation details and software frameworks, which could fall under cs.AR (Architecture) and cs.PL (Programming Languages). Additionally, the paper involves testing and measuring, which could fall under cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
